<p><b>Mott the Hoople</b> are an English rock band with strong <a href="/wiki/Rhythm_and_blues" title="Rhythm and blues">R&amp;B</a> roots, popular in the <a href="/wiki/Glam_rock" title="Glam rock">glam rock</a> era of the early to mid-1970s. They are probably best known for the song "<a href="/wiki/All_the_Young_Dudes" title="All the Young Dudes">All the Young Dudes</a>", written for them by <a href="/wiki/David_Bowie" title="David Bowie">David Bowie</a> and appearing on their 1972 <a href="/wiki/All_the_Young_Dudes_(album)" title="All the Young Dudes (album)">album of the same name</a>.</p>
<p></p>
